com.googlecode.cqengine.persistence.support.serialization

Class KryoSerializer<O>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.googlecode.cqengine.persistence.support.serialization.KryoSerializer<O>
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    PojoSerializer<O>

    public class KryoSerializer<O>
extends Object
implements PojoSerializer<O>
    Uses Kryo to serialize and deserialize objects; for use with CQEngine's disk and off-heap indexes and persistence.

    A validateObjectIsRoundTripSerializable(Object) method is also provided, to validate the compatibility of end-user POJOs with this serializer.

    Author:
    npgall

    • Constructor Detail

      • KryoSerializer

        public KryoSerializer(Class<O> objectType,
                      PersistenceConfig persistenceConfig)
        Creates a new Kryo serializer which is configured to serialize objects of the given type.
        Parameters:
        objectType - The type of the object
        persistenceConfig - Configuration for the serializer, in particular the polymorphic parameter which if true, causes Kryo to persist the name of the class with every object, to allow the collection to contain a mix of object types within an inheritance hierarchy; if false causes Kryo to skip persisting the name of the class and to assume all objects in the collection will be instances of the same class.

      • validateObjectIsRoundTripSerializable

        public static <O> void validateObjectIsRoundTripSerializable(O candidatePojo)
        Performs sanity tests on the given POJO object, to check if it can be serialized and deserialized with Kryo serialzier as used by CQEngine.

        If a POJO fails this test, then it typically means CQEngine will be unable to serialize or deserialize it, and thus the POJO can't be used with CQEngine's off-heap or disk indexes or persistence.

        Failing the test typically means the data structures or data types within the POJO are too complex. Simplifying the POJO will usually improve compatibility.

        This method will return normally if the POJO passes the tests, or will throw an exception if it fails.

        Parameters:
        candidatePojo - The POJO to test
